---
import ProductLayout from '../components/layout/ProductLayout.astro';

const now = new Date().toLocaleTimeString([], { hour: '2-digit', minute: '2-digit' });
---

<ProductLayout now={now} currentPath="/research">
  <section class="page-panel grid">
    <div class="page-copy">
      <span class="page-eyebrow">Research surface</span>
      <div>
        <div class="page-kicker">Research</div>
        <h1 class="page-headline">Light methodology framing without pretending a full portal exists.</h1>
      </div>
      <p>
        Research is now a first-class route so ThreatParallax reads like a product instead of a single
        dashboard shell. This page remains intentionally light until the methodology, cadence, and
        source framing are added in the next issue.
      </p>
      <p>
        The scope stays narrow for Phase II: credible positioning for security buyers, no padded
        archive, and no premature disclosures workflow.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="page-list">
      <div class="page-list-item">
        <strong>Planned in this phase</strong>
        <p>Methodology summary, source framing, and clear signals about research cadence.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="page-list-item">
        <strong>Not planned in this phase</strong>
        <p>Full CMS, advisory archive, or expanded disclosure operations.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="page-list-item">
        <strong>Reason for the route now</strong>
        <p>The product structure is established before deeper research content lands.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</ProductLayout>
